news.title: Arkade Developers acquires 6.28 acre land in Thane for ₹172.48 crore
news.para: The project has a gross development value (GDV) of ₹2,000 crore and have a RERA saleable area of 9.26 lakh sq ft.

news.title: Hyderabad records over ₹4,000 crore in property registrations in May 2025
news.para: Registrations for homes priced above ₹1 crore grew by 37% year-on-year, accounting for 19% of total registrations. In contrast, homes priced below ₹50 lakh and those in the ₹50 lakh to ₹1 crore range witnessed a decline in volumes, despite continuing to account for 55% and 26% of total sales, respectively.

news.title: Hrithik & Rakesh Roshan sell three properties in Mumbai for ₹6.75 crore
news.para: The first property, valued at ₹3.75 crore, is located in Veejays Niwas CHS and was sold by Rakesh Roshan. It has a built-up area of 95.26 sq meters (1,025 sq ft) and includes two car parking spaces.

news.title: Bengaluru: Banashankari allottees await legal resolution
news.para: The Karnataka High Court has passed the judgment in favour of original land owners, who claimed the BDA has failed to fully develop the land. With this hundreds of people who bought sites at Banashankari 6th Stage Layout are in trouble as the High Court quashed proceedings over acquisition of 16 acres of land.

news.title: Karnataka HC strikes down amendment laws on civic body’s retrospective levies
news.para: The 2021 Amendment Act was enacted to override the high court's earlier decision in the Sundaram Shetty case rendered in 2021, which declared the practice of linking levies to guidance value as illegal.

news.title: Goa gets sustainable heritage policy, private homes to benefit
news.para: The policy envisages including heritage conservation in academic curricula and promoting heritage tourism through curated experiences. The policy also includes incentives for private heritage properties.

news.title: Kochi metro phase III plan suffers setback after high DPR bid
news.para: As RITES, the lone bidder, quoted an amount more than double the estimated cost of DPR preparation, Kochi Metro Rail Ltd (KMRL) issued a re-tender inviting DPR consultancy.

news.title: HC dismisses Leela Group appeals against AAI eviction proceedings in Mumbai
news.para: The court observed that the lease period expired long ago, and eviction was not an issue amenable to arbitration under the lease agreement between AAI and Leela.

news.title: Gurugram: Illegal farmhouses & residential colonies thrive around Sultanpur lake buffer zone
news.para: Illegal plotting and development of farmhouses and colonies continue unabated in spite of repeated crackdowns and a complete ban on construction in this eco-sensitive zone.

news.title: About 40 homes in DLF-2 under government lens for illegal construction in Gurugram
news.para: However, sources in the enforcement wing said the department suspects the number of violators may exceed the current list of 40 homes.

news.title: Are you helping illegal constructions, Kolkata HC asks civic body
news.para: The unauthorised construction was on premises number 22, Sarat Bose Road. Car parking space at a building sanctioned as a residential structure was illegally converted into a commercial shop.

news.title: Zirakpur municipal council seals building in VIP Enclave for plan violation
news.para: According to municipal authorities, the builder had made unauthorised modifications and structural deviations despite having an approved building plan.

news.title: Now, transferable development rights can be used anywhere in Bengaluru
news.para: GBA, currently spread over 709 sq km, includes both core and peripheral regions under the restructured BBMP jurisdiction.

news.title: Hyderabad: Builders in limbo as jurisdiction tangle stalls layout approvals post HMDA expansion
news.para: ​A bureaucratic deadlock between two planning authorities—HMDA and the directorate of town and country planning (DTCP)—has left scores of building and layout applications in limbo, despite applicants having paid the required fees months earlier.

news.title: MHADA invites tenders for cluster redevelopment of Kamathipura in South Mumbai
news.para: The Kamathipura area, spread across 34 acres in South Mumbai, includes approximately 943 cess buildings in lanes 1 to 15, with around 6625 residential and 1376 non-residential tenants/residents, totaling 8,001.

news.title: Authorities raze 10 farm houses, five illegal structures in Aravalis
news.para: Illegal farm houses worth crores of rupees built on the road from Anand Van to Aravalli were razed on and about 10 acres of land was vacated, they said.

news.title: Hamirpur civic body to allot house numbers after property survey
news.para: Additional Deputy Commissioner-cum-Commissioner of Hamirpur Nagar Nigam, Abhishek Garg, said the process of assigning house numbers will begin as soon as the ward demarcation and property survey are completed.

news.title: Haryana CM hands over shop registries to 250 beneficiaries
news.para: According to an official statement, this step marks another milestone in empowering citizens through property ownership. Earlier, around 6,000 beneficiaries had received this benefit under the scheme.

news.title: Reliance Industries sells 3.64% stake in Asian Paints for ₹7,703 crore
news.para: Reliance Industries, through its affiliate Siddhant Commercials Pvt Ltd, sold 3.50 crore equity shares or 3.64 per cent stake in Asian Paints, as per the block deal data available with the National Stock Exchange (NSE).

news.title: Bank of Maharashtra slashes retail loan rate by up to 50 bps
news.para: The interest rate reduction by Pune-based lender is in line with the rate moderation done by RBI last week and the new rates are effective from June 10.
